How did you find out about Costa Rica and its surfing waves?
We have a lot of surfer friends, and I have a good friend who lives in Tamarindo, and the waves here are incredible.
My friends always go surfing in Costa Rica and Nicaragua, as well as in Mexico, these are great places to surf, that’s how we learned about it, from people who love surfing.
Looking at the tour, one can say that you have done great shows with a lot of songs.
What were you planning to do in Costa Rica?
Since we have never played there before, we have no limits on what we can do.
We will try to make the best show possible with a wide variety of songs; we will try to play a few songs from each album and present our fans with a wide variety of repertoire.
You never repeat a repertoire.
How does that work?
I think it’s partly because we have nine records and we can play more than 120 songs and everyone likes different songs, so it’s hard to choose which songs to play each night.
When we have two or three songs that we haven’t played for a while, it keeps us in tune and surprises us because it reminds us of the reasons why we loved those songs and what we could forget.
