How do you remember your other project, Manother Love Bone?
I think we’re writing really good songs and it was great in the beginning.
We were a band for almost three years and didn’t release a single album until the death of Andy (Andrew Woods).
There was a lot of disappointment for me because it lasted so long, and most importantly, we are still close friends with Bruce (Ferveser) and Greg (Gilmore) who have always had a lot of fun with us in the band, and when I hear a song or I see a picture, I think about it.
He was a wonderful man, and we miss him.
Local band Las Robertas will be responsible for opening the show in Costa Rica.
Is it true that you are familiar with her work, especially Eddie Wedder, and that's why you chose her for discovery?
Yes, the producers sent us a few videos, and it was a band that we liked the most, so we can’t wait to see what Las Robertas has to offer live, and it must be very exciting.
Why are you constantly changing the words in Yellow Ledbetter at concerts?
