France must build its opinion on objective facts and on rational data.
Now that we have 7,000 million people on the planet, demographic development will double the demand for electricity by 2050, unless a large part of the world’s population is deprived of vital elements.
During the same period, it will be necessary to compensate for the growing shortage of fossil fuels in order to continue the production of electricity constantly, not forgetting the crucial need to reduce greenhouse gas emissions in order to combat the climate imbalance - a theme that has disappeared from the ecological.
The Fukushima accident does not change any of these factors.
That’s why Germany remains alone in its decision to give up nuclear energy.
